<p>Neighborhoods like Kendall, Westchester, and Pinecrest feature many single-family homes with optimal south-facing roof orientations for solar panels. These areas typically have FPL service with standard net metering agreements. Coastal neighborhoods such as Key Biscayne and Miami Beach require HVAC systems with enhanced corrosion resistance due to salt air exposure, and solar panels may need more frequent cleaning due to sea spray. The Little Havana and Overtown areas offer excellent solar potential for smaller homes, with community solar programs helping make renewable energy more accessible to residents.</p>

